vernac_cmds: Require Import String Coqlib Maps Integers Floats Errors.
Require Import AST Values Memory Globalenvs Events.
Require Import SelectOp SelectOpproof SplitLong SplitLongproof.
Definition unary_constructor_sound (cstr: expr -> expr) (sem: val -> val) : Prop := forall le a x, eval_expr ge sp e m le a x -> exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (cstr a) v /\ Val.lessdef (sem x) v.

Definition binary_constructor_sound (cstr: expr -> expr -> expr) (sem: val -> val -> val) : Prop := forall le a x b y, eval_expr ge sp e m le a x -> eval_expr ge sp e m le b y -> exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (cstr a b) v /\ Val.lessdef (sem x y) v.

Definition partial_unary_constructor_sound (cstr: expr -> expr) (sem: val -> option val) : Prop := forall le a x y, eval_expr ge sp e m le a x -> sem x = Some y -> exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (cstr a) v /\ Val.lessdef y v.

Definition partial_binary_constructor_sound (cstr: expr -> expr -> expr) (sem: val -> val -> option val) : Prop := forall le a x b y z, eval_expr ge sp e m le a x -> eval_expr ge sp e m le b y -> sem x y = Some z -> exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (cstr a b) v /\ Val.lessdef z v.
Theorem eval_longconst: forall le n, eval_expr ge sp e m le (longconst n) (Vlong n).
Lemma is_longconst_sound: forall v a n le, is_longconst a = Some n -> eval_expr ge sp e m le a v -> v = Vlong n.
Theorem eval_andlimm: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (andlimm n) (fun v => Val.andl v (Vlong n)).
Theorem eval_orlimm: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (orlimm n) (fun v => Val.orl v (Vlong n)).
assert (DEFAULT: exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (Eop Oorl (a:::b:::Enil)) v /\ Val.lessdef (Val.orl x y) v) by TrivialExists.
assert (ROR: forall v n1 n2, Int.add n1 n2 = Int64.iwordsize' -> Val.lessdef (Val.orl (Val.shll v (Vint n1)) (Val.shrlu v (Vint n2))) (Val.rorl v (Vint n2))).
predSpec Int.eq Int.eq_spec (Int.add n1 n2) Int64.iwordsize'; auto.
predSpec Int.eq Int.eq_spec (Int.add n1 n2) Int64.iwordsize'; auto.
Theorem eval_xorlimm: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (xorlimm n) (fun v => Val.xorl v (Vlong n)).
Theorem eval_shllimm: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (fun e => shllimm e n) (fun v => Val.shll v (Vint n)).
subst n; destruct x; simpl; auto.
change (Int64.shl' i Int.zero) with (Int64.shl i Int64.zero).
assert (DEFAULT: exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (Eop (Oshllimm n) (a:::Enil)) v /\ Val.lessdef (Val.shll x (Vint n)) v) by TrivialExists.
destruct (Int.ltu (Int.add n n1) Int64.iwordsize') eqn:LT'; auto.
Theorem eval_shrluimm: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (fun e => shrluimm e n) (fun v => Val.shrlu v (Vint n)).
subst n; destruct x; simpl; auto.
change (Int64.shru' i Int.zero) with (Int64.shru i Int64.zero).
assert (DEFAULT: exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (Eop (Oshrluimm n) (a:::Enil)) v /\ Val.lessdef (Val.shrlu x (Vint n)) v) by TrivialExists.
destruct (Int.ltu (Int.add n n1) Int64.iwordsize') eqn:LT'; auto.
Theorem eval_shrlimm: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (fun e => shrlimm e n) (fun v => Val.shrl v (Vint n)).
subst n; destruct x; simpl; auto.
change (Int64.shr' i Int.zero) with (Int64.shr i Int64.zero).
assert (DEFAULT: exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (Eop (Oshrlimm n) (a:::Enil)) v /\ Val.lessdef (Val.shrl x (Vint n)) v) by TrivialExists.
destruct (Int.ltu (Int.add n n1) Int64.iwordsize') eqn:LT'; auto.
Theorem eval_addlimm: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (addlimm n) (fun v => Val.addl v (Vlong n)).
assert (A: forall x y, Int64.repr (x + y) = Int64.add (Int64.repr x) (Int64.repr y)).
intros; apply Int64.eqm_samerepr; auto with ints.
assert (B: forall id ofs n, Archi.ptr64 = true -> Genv.symbol_address ge id (Ptrofs.add ofs (Ptrofs.repr n)) = Val.addl (Genv.symbol_address ge id ofs) (Vlong (Int64.repr n))).
replace (Ptrofs.repr n) with (Ptrofs.of_int64 (Int64.repr n)) by auto with ptrofs.
red; intros; destruct (addl_match a b); InvEval.
red; intros; destruct (subl_match a b); InvEval.
Theorem eval_mullimm_base: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (mullimm_base n) (fun v => Val.mull v (Vlong n)).
destruct (Int64.one_bits' n) as [ | i [ | j [ | ? ? ]]] eqn:B.
replace (Val.mull x (Vlong n)) with (Val.shll x (Vint i)).
rewrite (Int64.one_bits'_range n) by (rewrite B; auto with coqlib).
assert (A0: eval_expr ge sp e m le' (Eletvar O) x) by (constructor; reflexivity).
rewrite (Int64.one_bits'_range n) in B1 by (rewrite B; auto with coqlib).
rewrite (Int64.one_bits'_range n) in B2 by (rewrite B; auto with coqlib).
Theorem eval_mullimm: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (mullimm n) (fun v => Val.mull v (Vlong n)).
red; intros; destruct (mull_match a b); InvEval.
Theorem eval_mullhu: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (fun a => mullhu a n) (fun v => Val.mullhu v (Vlong n)).
Theorem eval_mullhs: forall n, unary_constructor_sound (fun a => mullhs a n) (fun v => Val.mullhs v (Vlong n)).
Theorem eval_shrxlimm: forall le a n x z, eval_expr ge sp e m le a x -> Val.shrxl x (Vint n) = Some z -> exists v, eval_expr ge sp e m le (shrxlimm a n) v /\ Val.lessdef z v.
destruct x; simpl in H0; inv H0.
Theorem eval_cmplu: forall c le a x b y v, eval_expr ge sp e m le a x -> eval_expr ge sp e m le b y -> Val.cmplu (Mem.valid_pointer m) c x y = Some v -> eval_expr ge sp e m le (cmplu c a b) v.
destruct (Val.cmplu_bool (Mem.valid_pointer m) c x y) as [vb|] eqn:C; simpl in H1; inv H1.

destruct (is_longconst a) as [n1|] eqn:LC1; destruct (is_longconst b) as [n2|] eqn:LC2; try (assert (x = Vlong n1) by (eapply is_longconst_sound; eauto)); try (assert (y = Vlong n2) by (eapply is_longconst_sound; eauto)); subst.
Theorem eval_cmpl: forall c le a x b y v, eval_expr ge sp e m le a x -> eval_expr ge sp e m le b y -> Val.cmpl c x y = Some v -> eval_expr ge sp e m le (cmpl c a b) v.
destruct (Val.cmpl_bool c x y) as [vb|] eqn:C; simpl in H1; inv H1.
